  "body_excerpt": "If a non-contiguous buffer was passed to APIs which accepted Python buffers (e.g. `Hash.update()`), this could lead to buffer overflows. For example:\n\n```python\nh = Hash(SHA256())\nb.update(buf[::-1])\n```\n\nwould read past the end of the buffer on Python >3.11",
